## 3. API DESIGN

### 3.1 REST Principles (Stripe-style)

- Resources are **nouns**, never verbs: `/invoices`, `/customers`, `/charges`
- Actions that don't map to CRUD use sub-resources: `POST /invoices/:id/pay`, `POST /subscriptions/:id/cancel`
- Consistent plural resource names always
- Never expose internal IDs — use prefixed, opaque IDs: `cus_`, `inv_`, `ch_` (Stripe pattern)
- Version in the URL: `/v1/customers` — never in headers for REST

```
GET    /v1/customers              → list
POST   /v1/customers              → create
GET    /v1/customers/:id          → retrieve
PATCH  /v1/customers/:id          → update (partial)
DELETE /v1/customers/:id          → delete
POST   /v1/customers/:id/archive  → action
```

### 3.2 Request Validation

Validate at the boundary. Never trust input.

```typescript
// Zod (TypeScript) — validate and type simultaneously
const CreateChargeSchema = z.object({
  amount:      z.number().int().positive().max(99999999), // cents
  currency:    z.enum(["usd", "eur", "gbp"]),
  customerId:  z.string().regex(/^cus_[a-zA-Z0-9]+$/),
  description: z.string().max(500).optional(),
  metadata:    z.record(z.string()).optional(),
});

type CreateChargeInput = z.infer<typeof CreateChargeSchema>;

// Always validate before any business logic
const result = CreateChargeSchema.safeParse(req.body);
if (!result.success) {
  log.debug({ errors: result.error.flatten(), body: req.body }, "Request validation failed");
  return res.status(400).json(formatValidationError(result.error));
}
```

### 3.3 Response Shape

Consistent error shape everywhere — Stripe-style:

```typescript
// Success
{
  "id": "ch_abc123",
  "object": "charge",
  "amount": 5000,
  "currency": "usd",
  "status": "succeeded",
  "created": 1712345678
}

// Error
{
  "error": {
    "type":    "invalid_request_error",   // card_error | api_error | rate_limit_error
    "code":    "amount_too_small",        // machine-readable
    "message": "Amount must be at least $0.50",  // human-readable
    "param":   "amount",                  // field that caused it, if applicable
    "requestId": "req_abc123"             // always include for support
  }
}
```

### 3.4 Pagination

Always paginate list endpoints. Never return unbounded lists.

```typescript
// Cursor-based (preferred for large datasets — Stripe pattern)
GET /v1/charges?starting_after=ch_abc&limit=25

{
  "object": "list",
  "data": [...],
  "has_more": true,
  "url": "/v1/charges"
}

// Offset-based only for admin/internal tools where jumping to page N matters
GET /v1/admin/logs?page=3&per_page=50
```

