## 4. ERROR HANDLING

### 4.1 Error Taxonomy

```typescript
// Base — all errors extend this
class AppError extends Error {
  constructor(
    public readonly code:       string,
    public readonly message:    string,
    public readonly statusCode: number,
    public readonly context?:   Record<string, unknown>,
  ) { super(message); this.name = this.constructor.name; }
}

// Subtypes
class ValidationError    extends AppError { /* 400 */ }
class AuthenticationError extends AppError { /* 401 */ }
class AuthorizationError  extends AppError { /* 403 */ }
class NotFoundError       extends AppError { /* 404 */ }
class ConflictError       extends AppError { /* 409 */ }
class RateLimitError      extends AppError { /* 429 */ }
class ExternalServiceError extends AppError { /* 502 */ }
class InternalError       extends AppError { /* 500 */ }
```

### 4.2 Error Handling Rules

- **Never swallow errors silently.** Either handle, rethrow, or log + rethrow.
- **Wrap external errors** (DB, 3rd party) in your own error types — don't leak internal details.
- **Always include context** in errors: what was being attempted, with what inputs, at what state.
- **Log errors at the boundary** — not at every layer of the call stack (avoid duplicate logs).
- **Never expose stack traces to API consumers** in production.
- Distinguish **operational errors** (expected: user not found, card declined) from **programmer errors** (unexpected: null pointer, type mismatch) — handle them differently.

```typescript
// Global error handler
app.use((err: Error, req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
  const requestId = req.requestId;

  if (err instanceof AppError) {
    // Operational — expected failure path
    log.debug({ err: serializeError(err), requestId }, "Operational error");
    return res.status(err.statusCode).json(formatError(err, requestId));
  }

  // Programmer error — unexpected
  log.error({ err: serializeError(err), requestId, route: req.path }, "Unhandled error");
  metrics.increment("api.errors.unhandled", { route: req.path });

  res.status(500).json({
    error: {
      type:      "api_error",
      message:   "An unexpected error occurred",
      requestId,
    }
  });
});
```

