## 7. QUEUE & ASYNC JOBS

### 7.1 Job Design Rules

- Jobs must be **idempotent** — safe to run more than once.
- Jobs must be **atomic** — complete fully or not at all.
- Always include **job metadata** in every log: `jobId`, `queue`, `attempt`, `payload` (sanitized).
- Failed jobs go to a **Dead Letter Queue (DLQ)** — never silently discard.
- Always set **max retries** and **backoff strategy**.
- Jobs should be **small and focused** — one job, one responsibility.

```typescript
async function processPaymentJob(job: Job<PaymentPayload>) {
  const { jobId, attemptsMade, data } = job;
  const { invoiceId, customerId, amount } = data;

  log.debug({ jobId, attemptsMade, invoiceId, customerId, amount }, "Payment job started");

  try {
    const charge = await chargeCustomer({ invoiceId, customerId, amount });
    log.info({ jobId, invoiceId, chargeId: charge.id }, "Payment job completed");
    metrics.increment("jobs.payment.success");
  } catch (err) {
    log.error({ err, jobId, attemptsMade, invoiceId }, "Payment job failed");
    metrics.increment("jobs.payment.failure", { attempt: attemptsMade });
    throw err; // rethrow for retry
  }
}
```

### 7.2 Retry Strategy

```typescript
// Exponential backoff with jitter — prevents thundering herd
const retryOptions = {
  attempts:  5,
  backoff: {
    type:  "exponential",
    delay: 1_000,   // 1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, 16s
  },
};

// On final failure — DLQ
queue.on("failed", (job, err) => {
  log.error({ err, jobId: job.id, queue: job.queueName, payload: job.data }, "Job moved to DLQ");
  metrics.increment("jobs.dlq", { queue: job.queueName });
  alerting.notify("dlq.job.failed", { jobId: job.id, queue: job.queueName });
});
```

