## 8. RESILIENCE PATTERNS

### 8.1 Circuit Breaker

```typescript
const circuitBreaker = new CircuitBreaker(callStripeAPI, {
  timeout:             3_000,  // fail if no response in 3s
  errorThresholdPercentage: 50,  // open after 50% failures
  resetTimeout:        30_000, // retry after 30s
});

circuitBreaker.on("open",    () => log.warn({ service: "stripe" }, "Circuit breaker opened"));
circuitBreaker.on("close",   () => log.info({ service: "stripe" }, "Circuit breaker closed"));
circuitBreaker.on("halfOpen",() => log.debug({ service: "stripe" }, "Circuit breaker half-open"));
```

### 8.2 Timeouts

```typescript
// Always set timeouts on external calls. Never wait forever.
const response = await fetch(url, {
  signal: AbortSignal.timeout(5_000), // 5s max
});

// DB query timeout
await db.query("SET statement_timeout = '2000'"); // 2s per query
```

### 8.3 Rate Limiting

```typescript
// Sliding window rate limiter (Cloudflare / Upstash pattern)
const rateLimiter = new RateLimiter({
  redis,
  prefix:    "rl",
  limiter:   Ratelimit.slidingWindow(100, "1 m"), // 100 req/min
});

app.use(async (req, res, next) => {
  const identifier = req.ip ?? req.headers["cf-connecting-ip"];
  const { success, limit, remaining, reset } = await rateLimiter.limit(identifier);

  log.debug({ identifier, remaining, limit }, "Rate limit checked");

  res.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Limit",     limit);
  res.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Remaining", remaining);
  res.setHeader("X-RateLimit-Reset",     reset);

  if (!success) {
    log.warn({ identifier, limit }, "Rate limit exceeded");
    metrics.increment("api.rate_limit.exceeded");
    return res.status(429).json({ error: { type: "rate_limit_error", message: "Too many requests" } });
  }
  next();
});
```

