## 15. DO NOT

- ❌ `console.log` in production — use a structured logger always
- ❌ Swallow errors with empty `catch {}` blocks
- ❌ Use `SELECT *` in application queries — select only needed columns
- ❌ Mutate state without a transaction when multiple tables are involved
- ❌ Skip input validation because "it comes from our own service"
- ❌ Use synchronous file I/O (`fs.readFileSync`) in request handlers
- ❌ Hard-code credentials, secrets, or environment-specific config
- ❌ Write unbounded queries without `LIMIT`
- ❌ Deploy without health check endpoints
- ❌ Use `Date.now()` for unique IDs — use `ulid()` or `uuid()`
- ❌ Use `any` type in TypeScript — it defeats the type system
- ❌ Retry without backoff — you will take down your dependencies
- ❌ Return 200 with an error body — use correct HTTP status codes
- ❌ Log sensitive data — PII, tokens, passwords, card data
- ❌ Share DB connection pools across services
- ❌ Deploy schema migrations and code changes in the same deploy step
- ❌ Block the event loop with CPU-heavy work — offload to worker threads or a job queue

